subSubSection.paragraph:
Thorax
(
Figs 2
, 
11–12
). Prothorax black with yellow markings; anterior pronotal lobe mostly black with two small dorsolateral yellow spots; middle pronotal lobe with two midlateral yellow spots; posterior pronotal lobe in dorsal view divided into a central subtriangular part with narrow lateral arms originating near base and directed dorsally and lateral parts decumbent and projecting posteriorly (
Fig. 12
); in lateral view posterior pronotal lobe erect with tip slightly curving anteriorly (
Fig. 11
); smaller lateral lobe projecting posteriorly; propleuron yellow. Synthorax with a narrow yellow antehumeral stripe on mesepisternum; remainder of thorax as in male but lacking pruinosity and with metinfraepisternum mostly yellow (
Fig. 2
).
